    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And she put the skins of the kids of the goats upon his hands, etc.] Upon both his hands, and the whole of them that was bare, that he might appear to be like Esau: and upon the smooth of his neck; which in Esau was covered with hair as his hands; and Hiscuni, a Jewish writer f1433, observes, that the skins of goats are rough, and like the skin of a hairy man; and so Bochart f1434 remarks, that goats\u2019 hair in the eastern countries is not much unlike human [v_1Sa_19_13] hair; (see <091913>1 Samuel 19:13,16).\nVer.\n16. What four lessons for the flood itself?"
