    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And Rebekah took goodly garments of her eldest son Esau, etc.] Or \u201cdesirable\u201d f1431 ones, exceeding good ones: which [were] with her in the house; which she had the care and keeping of, and were wore only on particular occasions: some think these were priestly garments, which belonged to him as the firstborn, and were not in the keeping of his wives, being idolaters, but in his mother\u2019s keeping; which is not very probable, yet more likely than that they were, as some Jewish 486 writers f1432 say, the garments of Adam `[char_Adam_Luk_3]` the first man, which Esau seeing on Nimrod, greatly desired them, and slew him for them, (see <011010>Genesis 10:10); and hence called desirable garments: and put them upon Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` her younger son; that be might be took for Esau, should Isaac examine him and feel his garments, or smell them.\nVer.\n15. With whom does the prophet Ezekiel rank Noah `[char_Noah_Neh_6]` and on what characteristic?"
